      <div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA09d353n1-ptr" id="PJA09d353n1">1</a>
       
   <p>This letter should be compared with earlier ones from the Commissioners to Vergennes, <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-07-02-0196" class="document">[<ins title="editorial addition or explanation" class="ed">ante 20</ins>] Dec. 1778  [<ins title="editorial addition or explanation" class="ed">ante 9</ins>] Jan. 1779</a>, and from <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> to the Marquis de Lafayette of <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-07-02-0276" class="document">21 Feb. 1779</a> (vol. 7:292311, 421423); see also vol. 8:index, Adams, John: Military Interests, Naval matters. <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> sent a virtually identical copy of this letter, in Jonathan Loring Austins hand, to the Minister of Marine, Gabriel de Sartine (<span class="ref-terms" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;expan&gt;Archives Centrales de la Marine, Paris.&lt;/expan&gt; ]">Arch. de la Marine, Paris</span>, Campagnes B4, vol. 182), but no reply to that letter has been found.</p>

