      <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA09d353n13-ptr" id="PJA09d353n13">13</a>
       
   <p>Left blank. In July 1780, the garrison at New York reportedly comprised 20,048 troops, of which 14,285 were fit for duty (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Piers Mackesy, &lt;i&gt;The War for America, 17751783&lt;/i&gt;, Cambridge, 1965. ]">Mackesy, <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">War for America</span></span>, p. 346).</p>

